cs.MM, cs.DS, cs.SD, cs.IT, cs.LG 

The paper deals with convolution and cross-correlation, which are fundamental operations in multimedia signal processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also proposes a method for adjusting the imprecision of computation, which involves quantization and packing, indicating a possible fit with categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SD (Sound). The paper also discusses statistics and constraints on signal-to-noise ratio, suggesting a possible fit with categories such as cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
